@Ravette That’s also a very legit option! Medical science and forensic science always need bodies to be lovingly donated to help with research. ❤️

@Ravette There are also specific burial grounds for eco burials, which is essentially where you wrap the body in a shroud and place it in the earth and let it naturally decompose over time. The only thing with that is you don’t get to decide to plant things on top.

@Ravette Human composting is where they allow your body to naturally break down over the course of months, and is mixed together with organic materials to create viable soil. You can then use that to plant a tree on top of! This however is currently only legal in one state: Washington

@Ravette So the tree pods don’t really work as well as people think they do. The cremains interfere with the root ball of the tree and make it difficult to grow, and the tree ends up dying. HOWEVER! A better option is human composting. (Cont)

Idk maybe it’s my own abandonment issues that’s making me so emotional, but I can just relate so hard with Jinx that it hurts. Because I, too, would nuke buildings for the ones I love most.

That’s something that Jinx needed as a child that Vi couldn’t give to her, understandably. And I think those words are ultimately what seals in that ultimate decision to become Jinx. Because Jinx is perfect, and being Jinx, not Powder, is who was loved unconditionally.

And even in his LAST MOMENTS, where his own daughter had LITERALLY become his undoing, he tries to reassure her. Don’t cry. You’re perfect. He knows the guilt she’s feeling after once again killing someone she loves, so he uses his final moments to try to ease that pain.

Not because of what she could provide to him, but because he loved her. And I feel torn because his actions are BAD. He is not a Good Guy. But… he loves her. And don’t we all want someone to love us unconditionally, to be willing to let everything else burn?

He loved her in such an unconditional and flawed way. “They can all burn”. He was willing to let his life’s ambition burn for HER. And that’s something that Jinx needed, she needed someone to put her first, above anything else. And he was willing to that for her.
